messages.content:
For bare React Native, **react-native-firebase** (`@react-native-firebase/messaging`) is the way:

```bash
npm install @react-native-firebase/app @react-native-firebase/messaging
```

Setup:
1. Create Firebase project, download `google-services.json` (Android) and `GoogleService-Info.plist` (iOS)
2. Configure APNs key for iOS in Firebase Console
3. Request permissions and get FCM token:

```typescript
import messaging from '@react-native-firebase/messaging';

await messaging().requestPermission();
const token = await messaging().getToken();
// Send token to your backend

// Background handler
messaging().setBackgroundMessageHandler(async (msg) => {
  console.log('Background message:', msg);
});
```

Backend sending (Python):
```python
import firebase_admin
from firebase_admin import messaging
messaging.send(messaging.Message(
    notification=messaging.Notification(title="Hello", body="World"),
    token=device_token
))
```

FCM handles both Android and iOS (bridges to APNs). One API for both platforms.
